# Viral Food Directory - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Context
Building a map-first viral food discovery app for Malaysia.
Tech: Next.js 14 (App Router) + React + Tailwind CSS + Supabase + Google Maps API
Deadline: Wednesday, Dec 17, 2025

## Design System (ALWAYS FOLLOW)
- Primary: Teal #0D9488 (teal-600)
- Accent: Pink #EC4899 (pink-500) for viral/trending
- Background: #FAFAF8 light, #0F172A dark
- Border radius: rounded-2xl for cards, rounded-xl for buttons
- Padding: minimum p-6 (24px) for cards
- Shadows: shadow-sm default, shadow-md on hover
- Animations: 300ms duration, ease-out
- Font weights: 400, 500, 600, 700 only

## Component Rules
- Mobile-first responsive (base → md: → lg:)
- TypeScript strict (no 'any')
- Include loading states (skeleton preferred)
- Include error handling
- Dark mode support with dark: prefix

## API Route Rules
- All external API calls through /api routes
- Cache responses (5 min restaurants, 1 hour trending)
- Return format: { data, source: 'cache'|'database', count }
- Handle errors with try/catch, return { error: string }

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (FoodMarker.tsx)
- Routes: kebab-case (trending-dishes/route.ts)
- Utilities: camelCase (calculateDistance.ts)

